mdmIDTable.name: mdmIDTable
mdmIDTable.description: A list of modem ID entries.

mdmIDEntry.name: mdmIDEntry
mdmIDEntry.description: An Identification table entry, containing objects which define the identity and capabilities of a modem.

mdmIDIndex.name: mdmIDIndex
mdmIDIndex.description: A unique value for each modem configured in the system based on the values in the entity table in the USR extensions to the chassis mib.

mdmIDModel.name: mdmIDModel
mdmIDModel.description: Defines the model (ie. V.23, HST, etc.) of the modem represented by this row in the table.

mdmIDCountry.name: mdmIDCountry
mdmIDCountry.description: This object identifies the country or countries that this modem is designed for use in.

mdmIDHardwareSerNum.name: mdmIDHardwareSerNum
mdmIDHardwareSerNum.description: The modem's hardware serial number as stored in EEPROM.

mdmIDHardwareRev.name: mdmIDHardwareRev
mdmIDHardwareRev.description: The hardware revision of the modem as stored in the modem's EEPROM.

mdmIDSupervisorSwRev.name: mdmIDSupervisorSwRev
mdmIDSupervisorSwRev.description: The revision of the software being executed by the modem's supervisor processor.

mdmIDDataPumpSwRev.name: mdmIDDataPumpSwRev
mdmIDDataPumpSwRev.description: The revision of software being executed by the modem's data pump processor.

mdmIDIoProcessorSwRev.name: mdmIDIoProcessorSwRev
mdmIDIoProcessorSwRev.description: The revison of software being executed by the modem's IO Control Processor.

mdmLiTable.name: mdmLiTable
mdmLiTable.description: A list of configurable Line Interface objects for a modem. The number of table entries is given by modemNumber.

mdmLiEntry.name: mdmLiEntry
mdmLiEntry.description: Objects which define the line interface characteristics for a particualar modem.

mdmLiIndex.name: mdmLiIndex
mdmLiIndex.description: Index into the Line Interface table. This index is the value from the chassis mib entity relation table that is applicable for a particular modem.

mdmLiDialPause.name: mdmLiDialPause
mdmLiDialPause.description: Duration in seconds for the pause(') option in the dial command and the pause between command re-executions(> and A>) Default = 2. Equates to the modem's S8 register.

mdmLiCarrierRecDelay.name: mdmLiCarrierRecDelay
mdmLiCarrierRecDelay.description: Duration in 10ths of a second that the remote modem's carrier signal must be present before recognition. Ignored at speeds above 2400. Equates to the modem's S9 register. Default=6.

mdmLiCarrierLoss.name: mdmLiCarrierLoss
mdmLiCarrierLoss.description: Duration in 10ths of a second the modem waits after loss of carrier before hanging up. This allows the modem to distinguish between a momentary lapse in line quality and a true disconnect. When equal to 255 the modem will remain off hook until DTR drops or an ATH command is recieved. Equates to the modem's S10 register. Default=7.

mdmLiToneDialTiming.name: mdmLiToneDialTiming
mdmLiToneDialTiming.description: Duration and spacing in milliseconds of dialed Touch Tones. Equates to the modem's S10 register. Default=70.

mdmLiDteRxDataDelay.name: mdmLiDteRxDataDelay
mdmLiDteRxDataDelay.description: Duration in 10ths of a second that the modem inserts a RX transmission delay between CD and the first recieved character. Intended for custom applications and not recomended for general usage. Equates to the modem's S35 register. Default=0.

mdmLiTransmiter.name: mdmLiTransmiter
mdmLiTransmiter.description: Enables the modem to transmit data. Corresponds to the modem 'C' register. Default=2.

mdmLiDialMode.name: mdmLiDialMode
mdmLiDialMode.description: Determines whether the modem uses pulse or tone for dialing when initiating outgoing calls. Equates to the P and T registers in the modem. Default=0.

mdmLiGuardTone.name: mdmLiGuardTone
mdmLiGuardTone.description: This object is required for modems answering calls that originate from sites outside of North America. The modem's must be operating in either 1200 or 2400 bps and be using the V.32 answer sequence. This object defines what guard tone is used for answering calls. This object equates to the &G register in US Robotics modems. Default=none.

mdmLiLeasedLine.name: mdmLiLeasedLine
mdmLiLeasedLine.description: Enables modem to operate in leased line mode. When enabled the local an remote modems make a continuous connection without dialing. Should the connection be broken the modem's will attempt to automaticly reestablish it(see mdmCcLeasedLineRest). Equates to the modem's &L register Default = disabled.

mdmLiLeasedLineRestDelay.name: mdmLiLeasedLineRestDelay
mdmLiLeasedLineRestDelay.description: Sets the duration, in seconds, of the delay between when the modem senses loss of carrier and when it attempts to reestablish a leased line connection. The default setting of 15 should be appropriate for most installations.

mdmLiPulseMakeBreak.name: mdmLiPulseMakeBreak
mdmLiPulseMakeBreak.description: Determines the ratio of off hook to on hook interval for Pulse dialing. Equates to the modem's &P register. Default=North America.

mdmLiAnswerTone.name: mdmLiAnswerTone
mdmLiAnswerTone.description: Disables the 2100 Hz Answer tone allowing V.42 modems to connect more quickly and/or eliminating problems with older 2400-bps modems that do not recognise this tone. Equates to the modem's S27.3 register. Default=Enabled.

mdmLiRemoteEscGuardTime.name: mdmLiRemoteEscGuardTime
mdmLiRemoteEscGuardTime.description: Sets the duration in 20 millisecond increments of the guard time that the modem requires preceding and following the remote escape sequence. The default is 200 or 4 seconds.

mdmLiRemoteEscChar.name: mdmLiRemoteEscChar
mdmLiRemoteEscChar.description: Specifies the decimal value of the character used in the remote access escape code for entering online command mode on this modem from the remote site. Default = 126(~).

mdmLiRemAccessLimit.name: mdmLiRemAccessLimit
mdmLiRemAccessLimit.description: Determines the number of attempts to enter remote online command mode that are allowed for any one connection. The default is 0 which disables the remote access functon.

mdmLiRemPassword0.name: mdmLiRemPassword0
mdmLiRemPassword0.description: The password that allows a dial-in user to gain view only access to this modems parameters. A maximum of 8 characters is allowed.

mdmLiRemPassword1.name: mdmLiRemPassword1
mdmLiRemPassword1.description: The password used by a dial-in user to gain read-write access to this modems configuration. Maximum length is 8 characters.

mdmLiTransmitLevel.name: mdmLiTransmitLevel
mdmLiTransmitLevel.description: Specifies the signal level of the modem transmitter in negative db.

mdmLiSrc.name: mdmLiSrc
mdmLiSrc.description: Specifies either NIC or TDM as the source for the line interface.

mdmDcTable.name: mdmDcTable
mdmDcTable.description: A table of configurable objects that define the operation of Data Compression in the modem.

mdmDcEntry.name: mdmDcEntry
mdmDcEntry.description: Objects which define Data Compression operation for a modem.

mdmDcIndex.name: mdmDcIndex
mdmDcIndex.description: The index into the Data Compression table. This object contains the unique value for this modem as defined in the chassis mib entity relation table.

mdmDcDataCompression.name: mdmDcDataCompression
mdmDcDataCompression.description: Determines when and how data compression is enabled. Corresponds to the &K register in USR modems.

mdmTfTable.name: mdmTfTable
mdmTfTable.description: Table of test functions for modems. There is a table entry for each modem the quantity of which is specified by modemNumber.

mdmTfEntry.name: mdmTfEntry
mdmTfEntry.description: Objects used to request thet the modem perform certain diagnostic tests.

mdmTfIndex.name: mdmTfIndex
mdmTfIndex.description: A unique value used to identify this modem the value of which is determined by the entity table in the chassis mib and used as a method to index into the test function table.

mdmTfTestTime.name: mdmTfTestTime
mdmTfTestTime.description: Duration in seconds that the tests specified by mdmTfTestControl are to execute. Default=0(indefinate).

mdmTfV54.name: mdmTfV54
mdmTfV54.description: Corresponds to modem's &T register and provides tests specified by V.54. Default=normal.

mdmTfV54Errors.name: mdmTfV54Errors
mdmTfV54Errors.description: The number of errors occurring during the last V54 loopback test.

mdmTfDialInToneTest.name: mdmTfDialInToneTest
mdmTfDialInToneTest.description: This object is used to enable Dial in Tone Tests.

mdmTfToneTestCallRef.name: mdmTfToneTestCallRef
mdmTfToneTestCallRef.description: This object is used to send the call reference info with the tone test.

mdmTfToneIndex.name: mdmTfToneIndex
mdmTfToneIndex.description: A value used to ID this modem

mdmTfRspndrEntry.name: mdmTfRspndrEntry
mdmTfRspndrEntry.description: Objects containing the 105/102 responder test result dB levels and test status values.

mdmTfRspndrIndex.name: mdmTfRspndrIndex
mdmTfRspndrIndex.description: A value used to ID this modem.

mdmTf404FarNearLvl.description: 404 Hz tone at -16 dB loss test level. Far to near. Level in 0.1 dB resolution.

mdmTf404NearFarLvl.name: mdmTf404NearFarLvl
mdmTf404NearFarLvl.description: 404 Hz tone at -16 dB loss test level. Near to far. Level in 0.1 dB resolution.

mdmTfCmsgNearFarLvl.description: C-message test level. Near to far. Level in 0.1 dB resolution.

mdmTfCnotchFarNearLvl.description: C-notch test level. Far to near. Level in 0.1 dB resolution.

mdmTfCnotchNearFarLvl.description: C-notch test level. Near to far. Level in 0.1 dB resolution.

mdmtTfSigNoiseNearFarLvl.description: Signal to noise ratio level. Near to far. Level in 0.1 dB resolution.

mdmTf404NearFarSts.description: 404 Hz tone at -16 db loss test status. Near to far. Default=noTest(1).

mdmDiTable.name: mdmDiTable
mdmDiTable.description: Table of DTE interface objects. The number of table entries is specified by modemNumber.

mdmDiEntry.name: mdmDiEntry
mdmDiEntry.description: Objects that define the DTE interface for a modem.

mdmDiIndex.name: mdmDiIndex
mdmDiIndex.description: The index for the DTE interface table contains the unique value associated with this modem as defined in the chassis mib entity table.

mdmDiEscCodeGuardTime.name: mdmDiEscCodeGuardTime
mdmDiEscCodeGuardTime.description: Duration in 50ths of a second of idle time that must precede and follow the modem's command mode escape code. Default=50.

mdmDiLocalEscChar.name: mdmDiLocalEscChar
mdmDiLocalEscChar.description: Decimal equivalent of the character that is used to escape to on-line command mode. Values between 128 and 255 disable the escape code. Default=43(+).

mdmDiCarriageRetChar.name: mdmDiCarriageRetChar
mdmDiCarriageRetChar.description: Specifies the decimal equivalent of the carriage return character. Default=13.

mdmDiLineFeedChar.name: mdmDiLineFeedChar
mdmDiLineFeedChar.description: Specifies the decimal equivalent of the line feed character. Default=10.

mdmDiBackspaceChar.name: mdmDiBackspaceChar
mdmDiBackspaceChar.description: Specifies the decimal equivalent of the backspace character. Default=8.

mdmDiDelAsBackspace.name: mdmDiDelAsBackspace
mdmDiDelAsBackspace.description: Defines functionality of the delete key. Acts either to delete the character the cursor is currently on or acts the same as the backspace key. Default=delete.

mdmDiResetOnDtrEna.name: mdmDiResetOnDtrEna
mdmDiResetOnDtrEna.description: When enabled, this option will cause the modem to restart when the DTR control signal drops. Default=disabled.

mdmDiResultCodePauseDis.name: mdmDiResultCodePauseDis
mdmDiResultCodePauseDis.description: When enabled, the modem pauses 250ms before transmission of any result code. Default=enable.

mdmDiInterbridgeEna.name: mdmDiInterbridgeEna
mdmDiInterbridgeEna.description: When enabled, the modem operates in a mode that is compatible with an 'Appletalk InterBridge Network'. Default=disabled.

mdmDiBreakLen.name: mdmDiBreakLen
mdmDiBreakLen.description: Defines the duration of break characters that are sent to the DTE in ARQ mode. Defined in 10ms increments. Default=10(100ms).

mdmDiXonChar.name: mdmDiXonChar
mdmDiXonChar.description: Defines the decimal equivalent of the Xon character. This character will be used when software flow control is enabled. Default=17.

mdmDiXoffChar.name: mdmDiXoffChar
mdmDiXoffChar.description: Defines the decimal equivalent of the xoff character. This character will be used when software flow control is enabled. Default=19.

mdmDiDsrPulseTime.name: mdmDiDsrPulseTime
mdmDiDsrPulseTime.description: Duration in 20 millisecond increments that the DSR signal is pulsed when the modem is configured for pulsed DSR mode. Default=150.

mdmDiRtsCtsDelay.name: mdmDiRtsCtsDelay
mdmDiRtsCtsDelay.description: Duration in 10 millisecond increments that the modem delays setting CTS after detecting the presence of RTS. Default=1.

mdmDiHiSpeedResCodeEna.name: mdmDiHiSpeedResCodeEna
mdmDiHiSpeedResCodeEna.description: Determines if connection establishment result codes above 9600 are sent to the DTE. Default=enable.

mdmDiCmdLocalEchoEna.name: mdmDiCmdLocalEchoEna
mdmDiCmdLocalEchoEna.description: Defines whether or not the characters transmitted by the DTE are echoed back when in command mode. Default=disabled.

mdmDiDataModeEchoEna.name: mdmDiDataModeEchoEna
mdmDiDataModeEchoEna.description: Defines whether or not the DTE's transmitted data is echoed back durring a connection(half duplex). Default=disabled.

mdmDiDteDataRateMode.name: mdmDiDteDataRateMode
mdmDiDteDataRateMode.description: Defines how the modem determines the DTE data rate. When set to the default, follows link rate, the modem switches the DTE speed to match the link rate. When set to fixed, the DTE speed remains at the default DTE data rate or the rate of the last AT command. When set to ARQ fixed-Non ARQ follows the dte speed remains fixed for ARQ calls and follows the link rate for non ARQ calls.

mdmDiCdOverride.name: mdmDiCdOverride
mdmDiCdOverride.description: Defines the operation of the CD(Carrier Detect) signal. When overridden the CD signal is always asserted. Default=normal.

mdmDiDtrOverride.name: mdmDiDtrOverride
mdmDiDtrOverride.description: Defines operation with regard to DTR. When overridden the DTR signal is always assumed to be present. Default=normal.

mdmDiDsrOverride.name: mdmDiDsrOverride
mdmDiDsrOverride.description: Determines the functionality of the modem's DSR signal. Default=Override.

mdmDiEiaLineStatus.name: mdmDiEiaLineStatus
mdmDiEiaLineStatus.description: Provides a mechanism for the console to determine the current state of the DTE's EIA signals.

mdmDiTransmitFlowCntl.name: mdmDiTransmitFlowCntl
mdmDiTransmitFlowCntl.description: Determines if transmit flow control is enabled and if so whether it is hardware or software. Default=none.

mdmDiSoftwareRxFlowCntl.name: mdmDiSoftwareRxFlowCntl
mdmDiSoftwareRxFlowCntl.description: Determines if receive software flow control is enabled as well as what type. Default=none.

mdmDiHardwareRxFlowCntl.name: mdmDiHardwareRxFlowCntl
mdmDiHardwareRxFlowCntl.description: Determines if receive hardware flow control is enabled as well as how it is implemented. Default=RTS ignored.

mdmDiBreakHandling.name: mdmDiBreakHandling
mdmDiBreakHandling.description: Defines the method used to handle received breaks. When defined as destructive the modem's transmit data buffer is flushed. When defined as expidited, the break preceeds any pending data in the transmit buffer. Default=Destructive,Expidited.

mdmDiDteNvramLock.name: mdmDiDteNvramLock
mdmDiDteNvramLock.description: When locked, prohibits the DTE user from changing any of the NVRAM settings in the modem. Default=unlocked.

mdmDiSerialFormat.name: mdmDiSerialFormat
mdmDiSerialFormat.description: Defines the data bits and parity of the modem's DTE. Used in situations where the attached DTE is unable to send AT commands to initialize the DTE format. Default=8 bit no parity.

mdmDiDefaultDteDataRate.name: mdmDiDefaultDteDataRate
mdmDiDefaultDteDataRate.description: Defines the data rate of the DTE. Useful in those cases where the DTE is incapable of sending an AT command to initialize the data rate and a fixed data rate is required. Default=9600.

mdmDiRemAccessMsg.name: mdmDiRemAccessMsg
mdmDiRemAccessMsg.description: Specifies if the modem is to send the 'Modem Unavailable' message to the DTE when the DTE attempts to send data to a modem that is curently in command mode with a remote DTE. Default = enabled.

mdmDiV25DteDataRate.name: mdmDiV25DteDataRate
mdmDiV25DteDataRate.description: Defines the DTE Data Rates supported for V25 bis.

mdmDiSrc.name: mdmDiSrc
mdmDiSrc.description: Specifies either NIC or Packet Bus as the source for the DTE interface.

mdmDiSlot.name: mdmDiSlot
mdmDiSlot.description: Specifies the slot address as the DTE interface source when mdmdiSrc is configured for Packet Bus.

mdmDiBusyClock.name: mdmDiBusyClock
mdmDiBusyClock.description: specifies whether the modem will support either the current transmit clock or a new busy out.

mdmDiAtString.name: mdmDiAtString
mdmDiAtString.description: Provides an interface for issuing an AT command to the modem. Not implemented as a command so as to allow the object to be saved to NVRAM and subsequently configured during power-up.

mdmDiDtrRecognitionTime.name: mdmDiDtrRecognitionTime
mdmDiDtrRecognitionTime.description: S25 register tells the modem how quickly to react when DTR transitions from off to on. Default is 20. Increments are in 10 ms.

mdmScTable.name: mdmScTable
mdmScTable.description: Table of configurable objects which determine the operation of the Signal Converter. The quantity of entries in this table is defined by modemNumber.

mdmScEntry.name: mdmScEntry
mdmScEntry.description: Objects that define the operation of the modem's Signal Converter.

mdmScIndex.name: mdmScIndex
mdmScIndex.description: The unique value found in the chassis mib entity relation table that references this modem.

mdmScLinkRateSelect.name: mdmScLinkRateSelect
mdmScLinkRateSelect.description: Determines if the link will run at a fixed or variable data rate. Default=variable.

mdmScNonArqBufSize.name: mdmScNonArqBufSize
mdmScNonArqBufSize.description: Sets the sizer of the transmit buffer for non-ARQ mode operation to either 128 bytes or 1.5K. The smaller size is for low speed interactive applications, the large size is for file transfer. Default=128.

mdmScNonMnpDataCapture.name: mdmScNonMnpDataCapture
mdmScNonMnpDataCapture.description: Causes received characters to be buffered when the modem is attempting to negotiate an MNP call and the remote modem is not. Default=disabled.

mdmScSyncTimingSource.name: mdmScSyncTimingSource
mdmScSyncTimingSource.description: Specifies the clock source when operating in synchronous mode. Default=internal.

mdmScHstMod.name: mdmScHstMod
mdmScHstMod.description: May be used to disable HST operation on USRobotics Dual Standard modems. Default=enable.

mdmScHiFreqEq.name: mdmScHiFreqEq
mdmScHiFreqEq.description: Allows modem's high frequency equalization to be disabled if it causes problems on shorter lines. Default=enabled.

mdmScBackChanRate.name: mdmScBackChanRate
mdmScBackChanRate.description: Specifies the lower speed used in the asymetrical (HST) mode of operation. The 300 bps setting is provided for compatibility with early HST modems. Default=450.

mdmScV21Mod.name: mdmScV21Mod
mdmScV21Mod.description: When enabled, the modem will answer both bell 103 and V.21 calls but originates only V.21 calls. Default=disabled.

mdmScV32UnencodedMod.name: mdmScV32UnencodedMod
mdmScV32UnencodedMod.description: Allows unencoded modulation in V.32 mode. Although part of the CCITT V.32 recomendation it is rarely used. Default=disabled.

mdmScV32Mod.name: mdmScV32Mod
mdmScV32Mod.description: Allows V.32 modulation to be disabled on USRobotics Dual Standard modems. Default=enabled.

mdmScBell208.name: mdmScBell208
mdmScBell208.description: Allows modems that support Bell 208 modulation to include Bell 208 as part of the negotiation sequence. Default=Bell 208 disabled.

mdmScV32Bis.name: mdmScV32Bis
mdmScV32Bis.description: Allows V.32 bis modulation to be disabled. On USRobotics Dual Standard modems this may be useful in troublshooting HST operation. Default=V.32 bis enabled.

mdmScV32BisEnhance.name: mdmScV32BisEnhance
mdmScV32BisEnhance.description: Allows USRobotics V.32 Enahnced mode to be disabled for purposes of troubleshooting Default=enabled.

mdmScV32QuickRetrain.name: mdmScV32QuickRetrain
mdmScV32QuickRetrain.description: Allows the faster retrains that occur with USR's enhanced V.32 mode to be disabled for troubleshooting purposes. Default=enabled.

mdmScV23.name: mdmScV23
mdmScV23.description: Allows the modem to negotiate a V.23 connection(used in U.K.) after failing to negotiate a higher rate. Default=disabled.

mdmScHiSpeedModulation.name: mdmScHiSpeedModulation
mdmScHiSpeedModulation.description: Defines the handshaking options used in negotiation of high speed calls. Default=CCITT V.32

mdmScFallback.name: mdmScFallback
mdmScFallback.description: Defines whether or not the modem will be allowed to change protocols it detects a significant change in the line characteristics. If the modem is unable to maintain transmission with the current modulation technique it would fall back to a lower speed and if the line then improved it would upshift to a higher speed. Default=enabled.

mdmScV32TerboModeEnable.name: mdmScV32TerboModeEnable
mdmScV32TerboModeEnable.description: Allows the V32 Terbo mode to be disabled/enabled.

mdmScV34ModeEnable.name: mdmScV34ModeEnable
mdmScV34ModeEnable.description: Allows V34 mode to be disabled/enabled.

mdmScVFCSymRate2400.name: mdmScVFCSymRate2400
mdmScVFCSymRate2400.description: Allows the 2400 symbol rate to be disabled/enabled on V.FC modems.

mdmScVFCSymRate2743.name: mdmScVFCSymRate2743
mdmScVFCSymRate2743.description: Allows the 2743 symbol rate to be disabled/enabled on V.FC modems.

mdmScVFCSymRate2800.name: mdmScVFCSymRate2800
mdmScVFCSymRate2800.description: Allows the 2800 symbol rate to be disabled/enabled on V.FC modems.

mdmScVFCSymRate3000.name: mdmScVFCSymRate3000
mdmScVFCSymRate3000.description: Allows the 3000 symbol rate to be disabled/enabled on V.FC modems.

mdmScVFCSymRate3200.name: mdmScVFCSymRate3200
mdmScVFCSymRate3200.description: Allows the 3200 symbol rate to be disabled/enabled on V.FC modems.

mdmScVFCSymRate3429.name: mdmScVFCSymRate3429
mdmScVFCSymRate3429.description: Allows the 3429 symbol rate to be disabled/enabled on V.FC modems.

mdmScVFC8S2DMapping.name: mdmScVFC8S2DMapping
mdmScVFC8S2DMapping.description: Allows the 8S-2D mapping to be disabled/enabled on V.FC modems.

mdmScVFC16S4DMapping.name: mdmScVFC16S4DMapping
mdmScVFC16S4DMapping.description: Allows the 16S-4D mapping to be disabled/enabled on V.FC modems.

mdmScVFC32S2DMapping.name: mdmScVFC32S2DMapping
mdmScVFC32S2DMapping.description: Allows the 32S-2D mapping to be disabled/enabled on V.FC modems.

mdmScVFC64S4DMapping.name: mdmScVFC64S4DMapping
mdmScVFC64S4DMapping.description: Allows the 64S-4D mapping to be disabled/enabled on V.FC modems.

mdmScVFCNonLinearCoding.name: mdmScVFCNonLinearCoding
mdmScVFCNonLinearCoding.description: Allows the non-linear coding to be disabled/enabled on V.FC modems.

mdmScVFCTxLevelDeviation.name: mdmScVFCTxLevelDeviation
mdmScVFCTxLevelDeviation.description: Allows the TX level deviation to be disabled/enabled on V.FC modems.

mdmScVFCPreEmphasis.name: mdmScVFCPreEmphasis
mdmScVFCPreEmphasis.description: Allows the pre-emphasis to be disabled/enabled on V.FC modems.

mdmScVFCPreCoding.name: mdmScVFCPreCoding
mdmScVFCPreCoding.description: Allows the precoding to be disabled/enabled on V.FC modems.

mdmScVFCShaping.name: mdmScVFCShaping
mdmScVFCShaping.description: Allows the shaping to be disabled/enabled on V.FC modems.

mdmScVFCModeEnable.name: mdmScVFCModeEnable
mdmScVFCModeEnable.description: Allows to disable/enable V.FC mode in order to troubleshoot a connection.

mdmScV8.name: mdmScV8
mdmScV8.description: Allow V8 mode to be disabled/enabled

mdmSCV8CallIndicator.name: mdmSCV8CallIndicator
mdmSCV8CallIndicator.description: Allow V.8. call indicater to be disabled/enabled.

mdmScV34pModeEnable.name: mdmScV34pModeEnable
mdmScV34pModeEnable.description: Allows V34 plus modulation mode to be disabled. (default=0/enabled)

mdmSc300.name: mdmSc300
mdmSc300.description: Restrict 300 baud negotiations. Register S48.0 Default is disable (0) restriction.

mdmSc1200.name: mdmSc1200
mdmSc1200.description: Restrict 1200 baud negotiations. Register S48.1 Default is disable (0) restriction.

mdmSc2400.name: mdmSc2400
mdmSc2400.description: Restrict 2400 baud negotiations. Register S48.2 Default is disable (0) restriction.

mdmScHighSpeed.name: mdmScHighSpeed
mdmScHighSpeed.description: Restrict highspeed baud negotiations. Register S48.3 Default is disable (0) restriction.

mdmScSelectiveReject.name: mdmScSelectiveReject
mdmScSelectiveReject.description: Selective Reject register S51.6 is a function of the V.42/LAPM protocol. The default is enable (1)

mdmScPhExclusionDel.name: mdmScPhExclusionDel
mdmScPhExclusionDel.description: Enable/disable phone extension delay S51.7. Default is enable

mdmScLinkRateAmpU.name: mdmScLinkRateAmpU
mdmScLinkRateAmpU.description: Minimum high-speed direction link speed Default=variable.

mdmScX2HighPowerConst.name: mdmScX2HighPowerConst
mdmScX2HighPowerConst.description: This object is used to enable/disable the X2 high-power constellation. This object is only valid in countries, where it is legal. It corresponds to S Register 76.7 Default = Disable(1).

mdmScPiafs.name: mdmScPiafs
mdmScPiafs.description: This object is used to enable/disable PIAFS protocol. It corresponds to S Register 72.4 Default = enable(1).

mdmScPiafsV42bis.name: mdmScPiafsV42bis
mdmScPiafsV42bis.description: This object is used to enable/disable PIAFS V42bis compression protocol. It corresponds to S Register 72.5. Default = enable(1).

mdmScTxPwrLvl.name: mdmScTxPwrLvl
mdmScTxPwrLvl.description: This object configures the power level. It applies to S-register S82.

mdmScTxPwrLvlApplied.name: mdmScTxPwrLvlApplied
mdmScTxPwrLvlApplied.description: This object configures where the power level is applied. It applies to S-register S81.0.

mdmScX2Version2.name: mdmScX2Version2
mdmScX2Version2.description: This object is the x2 Version 2 Modulation. It applies to S-register S81.1

mdmScV34Fallback.name: mdmScV34Fallback
mdmScV34Fallback.description: This object is the x2 fallback to v34. It applies to S-register S76.3

mdmScV90Analogue.name: mdmScV90Analogue
mdmScV90Analogue.description: This object controls the enable/disable of the V.90 client modulation.Default=Enable(1).

mdmScV90Digital.name: mdmScV90Digital
mdmScV90Digital.description: This object controls the enable/disable of the V.90 server modulation.Default=Enable(1).

mdmScV90AllDigital.name: mdmScV90AllDigital
mdmScV90AllDigital.description: This object controls the enable/disable of the V.90 symmetric modulation. Default=Enable(1).

mdmCcTable.name: mdmCcTable
mdmCcTable.description: A table containing the call control parameters for each modem in the chassis.

mdmCcEntry.name: mdmCcEntry
mdmCcEntry.description: Call control parameters for a modem. These define the sequence of operation related to how a call is negotiated.

mdmCcIndex.name: mdmCcIndex
mdmCcIndex.description: The index which uniquely identifies the modem to which this entry is applicable. The value corresponds to the value of the index to the entity table in the chassis MIB that corresponds to the same modem.

mdmCcDialDelay.name: mdmCcDialDelay
mdmCcDialDelay.description: Defines the number of seconds the modem waits between going off hook and begining to dial. Ignored when result code options 2,4,6,or 7 are active. Default=2.

mdmCcWaitForCarrier.name: mdmCcWaitForCarrier
mdmCcWaitForCarrier.description: Defines the number of seconds the modem will wait for a carrier signal after dialing. Default=60.

mdmCcInactivityTimer.name: mdmCcInactivityTimer
mdmCcInactivityTimer.description: Sets the duration (in seconds) that the modem will maintain a connection when there is no activity on the phone line. The feature is disabled when set to 0. Default=0.

mdmCcAutoDialOnDtrEna.name: mdmCcAutoDialOnDtrEna
mdmCcAutoDialOnDtrEna.description: When enabled the modem will dial the number present in mdmCCPhoneString0 when the DTR signal transitions from low to high. Default=disable(1).

mdmCcAutoDialOnPwrUpEna.name: mdmCcAutoDialOnPwrUpEna
mdmCcAutoDialOnPwrUpEna.description: When enabled, the modem will dial the number present in mdmCcPhoneString0 on power up or after a reset. Default=disable(1).

mdmCcGhostPortLockEna.name: mdmCcGhostPortLockEna
mdmCcGhostPortLockEna.description: When enabled, the modem requires that DTR go low before it will accept another call. The modem also implements a Fast Connect mode where CD is asserted before the link negotiation is complete. Default=disable(1).

mdmCcQuietResultCodes.name: mdmCcQuietResultCodes
mdmCcQuietResultCodes.description: Determines whether or not the modem transmits result codes to the DTE. Default=noResult(2).

mdmCcResponseMode.name: mdmCcResponseMode
mdmCcResponseMode.description: Determines whether the modem transmits result codes in the verbal or numeric mode. Default=verbal(2).

mdmCcResultCodeOptions.name: mdmCcResultCodeOptions
mdmCcResultCodeOptions.description: Defines one of eight result code subsets and also defines indirectly how the modem reacts to dial tone etc. Equates to the modem's X register Default=1.

mdmCcArqResultCodeMode.name: mdmCcArqResultCodeMode
mdmCcArqResultCodeMode.description: Defines whether or not the ARQ result codes are sent to the DTE on connection(if result codes are enabled). Default=arqResultsEnabled(2).

mdmCcEscCodeRsp.name: mdmCcEscCodeRsp
mdmCcEscCodeRsp.description: Defines the action of the modem in response to the escape code(+++). The default value is determined by the state of Dip switch 2-3 on power up.

mdmCcAtRecognition.name: mdmCcAtRecognition
mdmCcAtRecognition.description: Determines which, if any, AT commands the modem will recognize or accept from the DTE. Default=ignore(1).

mdmCcMgmtSysMsgDis.name: mdmCcMgmtSysMsgDis
mdmCcMgmtSysMsgDis.description: Determines if the modem is to send special result codes, triggered by user conflicts with the management system, to the DTE. Default=enable(1).

mdmCcV32ToneDuration.name: mdmCcV32ToneDuration
mdmCcV32ToneDuration.description: Specifies the duration (in 10ths of a second) that the modem transmits the 3000/600 Hz answer tones for V.32 handshaking. A setting of 0 eliminates these tones and will result in faster connect times for V.21 and V.23 calls. Default=8.

mdmCcAutoAnswer.name: mdmCcAutoAnswer
mdmCcAutoAnswer.description: Determines the number of rings that the modem will answer calls on. When set to 0 the modem can only originate calls. Default=1.

mdmCcAnswerInOrigMode.name: mdmCcAnswerInOrigMode
mdmCcAnswerInOrigMode.description: When enabled the modem will answer calls using the sequence normaly used by the originating modem. Default=disable(1).

mdmCcArqBufWait.name: mdmCcArqBufWait
mdmCcArqBufWait.description: Sets the duration (in seconds) that the modem waits on an ARQ call before clearing the transmit buffer and dropping carrier after DTR drops. This is to allow time for the remote modem to acknowledge receipt of all transmitted data. Default=0.

mdmCcPhoneString0.name: mdmCcPhoneString0
mdmCcPhoneString0.description: Phone number stored in modem's non volitile memory. Useful in providing quick access to frequently called numbers. In addition mdmCcPhoneString0 is used for the dial on power up and dial on DTR options.

mdmCcPhoneString1.name: mdmCcPhoneString1
mdmCcPhoneString1.description: Phone number stored in the modem's non volitile memory, useful for providing quick access to frequently called numbers.

mdmCcPhoneString2.name: mdmCcPhoneString2
mdmCcPhoneString2.description: Phone number stored in the modem's non volitile memory, useful in providing quick access to frequently called numbers.

mdmCcPhoneString3.name: mdmCcPhoneString3
mdmCcPhoneString3.description: Phone number stored in the modem's non volitile memory, useful in providing quick access to frequently called numbers.

mdmCcErrorCntlMode.name: mdmCcErrorCntlMode
mdmCcErrorCntlMode.description: Defines if the modem is operating in synchronous or asynchronous mode and how it responds relative to negotiation of error control on asynchronous connections. When set to the default, normalArq(3), the modem attempts to connect with error control but if unable to negotiate it connects anyway. When set to none(1), async connections do not attempt to use error control. When set to arqOnly(4), the modem will hang up if unable to negotiate error contol. When set to syncMode(2), the modem will not connect asynchronously.

mdmCcMiMic.name: mdmCcMiMic
mdmCcMiMic.description: Specifies whether the modem will recognize MI/MIC closure as the mechanism for detecting incomming calls. Default=disable(1).

mdmCcMnpWith1200.name: mdmCcMnpWith1200
mdmCcMnpWith1200.description: Determines if the modem will include MNP/V42 negotiation on 1200 bps connections. Default=enable(1).

mdmCcMnpWith2400.name: mdmCcMnpWith2400
mdmCcMnpWith2400.description: Determines if the modem will include MNP/V43 negotiation on 2400 bps calls. default=enable(1).

mdmCcMnpWithV32.name: mdmCcMnpWithV32
mdmCcMnpWithV32.description: Determines if the modem will include MNP/V42 negotiation on V.32 connections. Default=enable(1).

mdmCcMnpTimeout.name: mdmCcMnpTimeout
mdmCcMnpTimeout.description: Specifies the MNP/V42 link request timeout for negotiation of 1200 and 2400 bps calls. Default=5.

mdmCcV21V23FallBackTimer.name: mdmCcV21V23FallBackTimer
mdmCcV21V23FallBackTimer.description: V21/V23 fallback timer, 1/10 sec. NVRAM S Register S29. Default=20

mdmCcAddnlAnswToneDur.name: mdmCcAddnlAnswToneDur
mdmCcAddnlAnswToneDur.description: Additional answer tone duration, 1/10 sec. NVRAM S Register S49. Default=16.

mdmCcBillingDelayPeriod.name: mdmCcBillingDelayPeriod
mdmCcBillingDelayPeriod.description: Billing Delay Period. 1/50 sec. NVRAM S Register S50. Default=100.

mdmCcCarrierAccessCode1.name: mdmCcCarrierAccessCode1
mdmCcCarrierAccessCode1.description: The DNIS Carrier Access Code (CAC) Number. This is a string which contains a number from 1 to 10 digits (e.g. 9501755). This is the 1st of 3 CACs.

mdmCcCarrierAccessCode2.name: mdmCcCarrierAccessCode2
mdmCcCarrierAccessCode2.description: The DNIS Carrier Access Code (CAC) Number. This is a string which contains a number from 1 to 10 digits. This is the 2nd of 3 CACs.

mdmCcCarrierAccessCode3.name: mdmCcCarrierAccessCode3
mdmCcCarrierAccessCode3.description: The DNIS Carrier Access Code (CAC) Number. This is a string which contains a number from 1 to 10 digits. This is the 3rd of 3 CACs.

mdmCcCallingInitStr1.name: mdmCcCallingInitStr1
mdmCcCallingInitStr1.description: This is the Carrier Access Code (CAC) initialization string. This string is a configuration string of 1 to 30 characters (e.g. &F, &F&B1&R1, etc.) This string does NOT include the AT attention prefix. This is the 1st of 4 CAC init strings.

mdmCcCallingInitStr2.name: mdmCcCallingInitStr2
mdmCcCallingInitStr2.description: This is the Carrier Access Code (CAC) initialization string. This string is 1 to 30 characters. It does NOT include the AT attention prefix. It is the 2nd of 4 CAC init strings.

mdmCcCallingInitStr3.name: mdmCcCallingInitStr3
mdmCcCallingInitStr3.description: This is the Carrier Access Code (CAC) initialization string. This is a string of 1 to 30 characters. It does NOT include the AT attention prefix. This is the 3rd of 4 CAC init strings.

mdmCcCallingInitStr4.name: mdmCcCallingInitStr4
mdmCcCallingInitStr4.description: This is the Carrier Access Code (CAC) initialization string. This is a string of 1 to 30 characters. It does NOT include the AT attention prefix. This is the 4th of 4 CAC init strings.

mdmCcDataFaxMode.name: mdmCcDataFaxMode
mdmCcDataFaxMode.description: Gives the current Data/FAX mode of the modem.

mdmCcT1CallSetupProc.name: mdmCcT1CallSetupProc
mdmCcT1CallSetupProc.description: Determines T1 call setup procedures used. Choices are 'normal' or 'none'. None assumes a dedicated (leased) DS0 assigned to the modem. Default=normalSetup(1).

mdmCcT1DialToneType.name: mdmCcT1DialToneType
mdmCcT1DialToneType.description: Determines if MF or DTMF tones are used for T1 signaling. Default = mfTones(1).

mdmCcT1KpStMfTones.name: mdmCcT1KpStMfTones
mdmCcT1KpStMfTones.description: Determines the usage of KP and ST MF tone encapsulation of the dial sequence. Default=enable(1).

mdmCcT1CallInitStrUse.name: mdmCcT1CallInitStrUse
mdmCcT1CallInitStrUse.description: Determines if calling init strings are used or not. Default=enable(1).

mdmCcT1CallInitStrBase.name: mdmCcT1CallInitStrBase
mdmCcT1CallInitStrBase.description: Determines if the calling init strings are based upon DNIS or ANI. Default=dnisBase(1).

mdmCcIntBlackListDis.name: mdmCcIntBlackListDis
mdmCcIntBlackListDis.description: Disable BlackList restriction in the international modems. Default=0 (enable) s40.1 reg

mdmCcOffHookRestrict.name: mdmCcOffHookRestrict
mdmCcOffHookRestrict.description: Disable off-hook restriction in the international modems. Default=0 (enable) S40.2 reg

mdmCcT1DialInAniDig.name: mdmCcT1DialInAniDig
mdmCcT1DialInAniDig.description: Sets the number of ANI digits allowed in incoming calls. Default = 0.

mdmCcT1DialInDnisDig.name: mdmCcT1DialInDnisDig
mdmCcT1DialInDnisDig.description: Sets the number of DNIS/DID digits allowed in incoming calls. Default = 0.

mdmCcNoPbNoConnEna.name: mdmCcNoPbNoConnEna
mdmCcNoPbNoConnEna.description: Sets if to answer a call when there is no Packet Bus link. Normal is the Default =0

mdmCcIdleDiscPatt.name: mdmCcIdleDiscPatt
mdmCcIdleDiscPatt.description: Idle disconnect pattern sent to the T1 NAC. Normal values: USA = 1, international = 84. Default = 1. Configure the T1 identically. Consult the help screen, user manual or US Robotics before changing. Modem register S71.

mdmCcMnp10.name: mdmCcMnp10
mdmCcMnp10.description: S61.4 register disable/enable MNP10 originate mode.

mdmCcMnp10Ec.name: mdmCcMnp10Ec
mdmCcMnp10Ec.description: S61.5 register disable/enable MNP10EC originate mode.

mdmCcAtzPbHandling.name: mdmCcAtzPbHandling
mdmCcAtzPbHandling.description: ATZ handling over Packet Bus. S72 REG

mdmCcExtDTMFToneSupport.name: mdmCcExtDTMFToneSupport
mdmCcExtDTMFToneSupport.description: Enable/Disable DTMF extended support. Default = disable

mdmCcDataOverVoice.name: mdmCcDataOverVoice
mdmCcDataOverVoice.description: Data Over Voice support originate S68.1.

mdmCc2100AnswerTone.name: mdmCc2100AnswerTone
mdmCc2100AnswerTone.description: Data Over Voice support answer S68.2.

mdmCcHdlcLicIe.name: mdmCcHdlcLicIe
mdmCcHdlcLicIe.description: This object is to Enable\Disable LIC IE message for HDLC protocols. S Register S68.3

mdmCcDtmfTerminationTone.name: mdmCcDtmfTerminationTone
mdmCcDtmfTerminationTone.description: This object is to set the DTMF Termination Tone.

mdmCcAfaxMaxRateSrvOpt20.name: mdmCcAfaxMaxRateSrvOpt20
mdmCcAfaxMaxRateSrvOpt20.description: This object is used to limit the maximum rate for an Analog Fax Connection. Service option 20. Upper nibble of the S94 register.

mdmCcAfaxMaxRateSrvOpt21.name: mdmCcAfaxMaxRateSrvOpt21
mdmCcAfaxMaxRateSrvOpt21.description: This object is used to limit the maximum rate for an Analog Fax Connection. Service option 21. Lower nibble of S94 register.

mdmEcTable.name: mdmEcTable
mdmEcTable.description: A table of Error Control Parameters for each modem in this system, the quantity of entries is given by modemNumber.

mdmEcEntry.name: mdmEcEntry
mdmEcEntry.description: Configurable objects which define the modems error control operation.

mdmEcIndex.name: mdmEcIndex
mdmEcIndex.description: This object contains the unique value assigned to this modem in the chassis mib entity relation table and is used as the mechanism for correctly indexing into this table.

mdmEcMnp3Dis.name: mdmEcMnp3Dis
mdmEcMnp3Dis.description: Determines if the modem will negotiate for MNP level 3 error correction. Default=enable.

mdmEcMnp4Dis.name: mdmEcMnp4Dis
mdmEcMnp4Dis.description: Determines if the modem will negotiate for MNP level 4 error correction. Default=enable.

mdmEcMnpUnusual.name: mdmEcMnpUnusual
mdmEcMnpUnusual.description: Determines if the modem will attempt to negotiate for MNP operation used in some early 2400bps modems. Default=disable.

mdmEcV42MnpHandshake.name: mdmEcV42MnpHandshake
mdmEcV42MnpHandshake.description: Determines what types of error correction the modem will attempt to negotiate. When configured for the default, full V.42 and MNP, the modem first tries to connect with V42 error control and then with MNP error control. When set to disable either V42 or MNP the modem will only attempt to negotiate the enabled protocol. When set to disable the V42 detect phase, it is not included in the handshaking process. This allows for faster connections between V42 modems.

mdmCsTable.name: mdmCsTable
mdmCsTable.description: A table of modem status and call statistic parameters for each modem in the chassis.

mdmCsEntry.name: mdmCsEntry
mdmCsEntry.description: Objects that define the modem status and statistics specific to a the current connection when the modem is on line or to the last connection when the modem is idle.

mdmCsIndex.name: mdmCsIndex
mdmCsIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the modem to which this entry is applicable. The value corresponds to the index of the same modem in the entity table of the chassis MIB.

mdmCsStatus.name: mdmCsStatus
mdmCsStatus.description: Current status of a modem including presence(idle), availability(disabled), and call progress states.

mdmCsLastNumberDialedOut.name: mdmCsLastNumberDialedOut
mdmCsLastNumberDialedOut.description: An ASCII string which represents the last phone number dialed by the modem.

mdmCsLastNumberDialedIn.name: mdmCsLastNumberDialedIn
mdmCsLastNumberDialedIn.description: An ASCII string representing the last number dialed in(if known). This is the 950-xxx (DNIS) number.

mdmCsLastCallingPartyNum.name: mdmCsLastCallingPartyNum
mdmCsLastCallingPartyNum.description: An ASCII string representing the current or last party that called this modem. Only known in ANI applications.

mdmCsOriginateAnswer.name: mdmCsOriginateAnswer
mdmCsOriginateAnswer.description: Defines whether the last or current call was originated or answered.

mdmCsRings.name: mdmCsRings
mdmCsRings.description: Defines the quantity of rings detected before the DTE answered with DTR on the last incomming call.

mdmCsDisconnectReason.name: mdmCsDisconnectReason
mdmCsDisconnectReason.description: Defines the reason that the last call was terminated.

mdmCsConnectFailReason.name: mdmCsConnectFailReason
mdmCsConnectFailReason.description: Defines the reason for failure if indeed the last call attempt failed.

mdmCsInitialTxLinkRate.name: mdmCsInitialTxLinkRate
mdmCsInitialTxLinkRate.description: The transmit speed at which the modem initialy connected on it's last or current call.

mdmCsInitialRxLinkRate.name: mdmCsInitialRxLinkRate
mdmCsInitialRxLinkRate.description: The receive speed at which the modem initialy connected on it's previous or current call.

mdmCsFinalTxLinkRate.name: mdmCsFinalTxLinkRate
mdmCsFinalTxLinkRate.description: The current transmit link rate of a connection, or the last link rate of the last connection.

mdmCsFinalRxLinkRate.name: mdmCsFinalRxLinkRate
mdmCsFinalRxLinkRate.description: The current receive link rate of a connection, or the last link rate of the last connection.

mdmCsModulationType.name: mdmCsModulationType
mdmCsModulationType.description: Specifies the current/final modulation type of the current or last call. The value can be different from the object mdmCsInitModulationType only for X2/V.90 calls.

mdmCsSyncAsyncModeUsed.name: mdmCsSyncAsyncModeUsed
mdmCsSyncAsyncModeUsed.description: Defines whether the current or last call was synchronous or asynchronous.

mdmCsErrorControlType.name: mdmCsErrorControlType
mdmCsErrorControlType.description: Specifies the Error control settings in the current or last call. (short form)

mdmCsCompressionType.name: mdmCsCompressionType
mdmCsCompressionType.description: Specifies the data compression used in the current or last call. (short format)

mdmCsEqualizationType.name: mdmCsEqualizationType
mdmCsEqualizationType.description: Specifies the equalization used in the current or last call.

mdmCsFallbackEnabled.name: mdmCsFallbackEnabled
mdmCsFallbackEnabled.description: Specifies whether line speed fallbacks were negotiated on the current or previous call.

mdmCsCharsSent.name: mdmCsCharsSent
mdmCsCharsSent.description: Specifies the number of characters sent on the current or previous call.

mdmCsCharsReceived.name: mdmCsCharsReceived
mdmCsCharsReceived.description: Specifies the number of characters received in the current or previous call.

mdmCsOctetsSent.name: mdmCsOctetsSent
mdmCsOctetsSent.description: Specifies the number of octets sent in the current or previous call.

mdmCsOctetsReceived.name: mdmCsOctetsReceived
mdmCsOctetsReceived.description: Specifies the number of octets received in the current or previous call.

mdmCsBlocksSent.name: mdmCsBlocksSent
mdmCsBlocksSent.description: Specifies the number of blocks sent in the current or previous call.

mdmCsBlocksReceived.name: mdmCsBlocksReceived
mdmCsBlocksReceived.description: Specifies the number of blocks received in the current or previous call.

mdmCsBlocksResent.name: mdmCsBlocksResent
mdmCsBlocksResent.description: Specifies the number of blocks the modem has had to retransmit due to block errors or timeouts in the current or previous call.

mdmCsRetrainsRequested.name: mdmCsRetrainsRequested
mdmCsRetrainsRequested.description: Specifies the number of retrains requested in the current or previous call.

mdmCsRetrainsGranted.name: mdmCsRetrainsGranted
mdmCsRetrainsGranted.description: Specifies the number of retrains granted in the current or previous call.

mdmCsLineReversalQty.name: mdmCsLineReversalQty
mdmCsLineReversalQty.description: Specifies the number of times the HST high and low speeds directions have been reversed in the current or previous call.

mdmCsCharsLost.name: mdmCsCharsLost
mdmCsCharsLost.description: Specifies the number of characters lost on the current or previous call. Not meaningful on synchronous calls.

mdmCsBackChannelRate.name: mdmCsBackChannelRate
mdmCsBackChannelRate.description: Specifies the negotiated HST back channel speed on the current or previous call.

mdmCsBlerQty.name: mdmCsBlerQty
mdmCsBlerQty.description: Specifies the number of block errors received on the link in the current or last call.

mdmCsLinkTimeoutQty.name: mdmCsLinkTimeoutQty
mdmCsLinkTimeoutQty.description: Specifies the number of link protocol timeouts on the current or previous call.

mdmCsFallbackQty.name: mdmCsFallbackQty
mdmCsFallbackQty.description: Specifies the quantity of link speed fallbacks that occured on the current or previous call.

mdmCsUpshiftQty.name: mdmCsUpshiftQty
mdmCsUpshiftQty.description: Specifies the number of link speed upshifts have occured in the current or previous call.

mdmCsLinkNakQty.name: mdmCsLinkNakQty
mdmCsLinkNakQty.description: Specifies the quantity of negative acknowledgements sent in response to errored blocks received on the link in the current or previous call.

mdmCsGainHitCount.name: mdmCsGainHitCount
mdmCsGainHitCount.description: The modem calculates the gain that is required to adjust the received signal to the ideal level. This defines the number of times that the gain was recalculated durring the current or previous call.

mdmCsSecurityUserName.name: mdmCsSecurityUserName
mdmCsSecurityUserName.description: The last dial security user that initiated the Call. This object is not saved to NVRAM.

mdmCsCallDuration.name: mdmCsCallDuration
mdmCsCallDuration.description: This is the length of the call in hh:mm:ss format. The maximum value reported will be 9999:59:59.

mdmCsQTimingOffset.name: mdmCsQTimingOffset
mdmCsQTimingOffset.description: Timing Offset in parts per million.

mdmCsX2signature.name: mdmCsX2signature
mdmCsX2signature.description: X2 diagnostics information from modem in hex.

mdmCsCallStartTime.name: mdmCsCallStartTime
mdmCsCallStartTime.description: Call started time in GMT format.

mdmCsCallEndTime.name: mdmCsCallEndTime
mdmCsCallEndTime.description: Call Ended time in GMT format.

mdmCsDigitalPadAttenuated.name: mdmCsDigitalPadAttenuated
mdmCsDigitalPadAttenuated.description: Attenuation of the digital pad in tenths of DB.

mdmCsInitModulationType.name: mdmCsInitModulationType
mdmCsInitModulationType.description: Specifies the modulation type of the current or last call. The value can be different from the object mdmCsModulationType only for X2/V.90 calls.

mdmCsCollectedDTMFDigits.name: mdmCsCollectedDTMFDigits
mdmCsCollectedDTMFDigits.description: This object is an ASCII array of the DTMF digits collected from the client.

mdmEvEntry.name: mdmEvEntry
mdmEvEntry.description: Modem events that can be managed.

mdmEvWatchdogTimouts.name: mdmEvWatchdogTimouts
mdmEvWatchdogTimouts.description: Quantity of times that a watchdog timeout has been detected for this modem.

mdmEvDteIdleTimouts.name: mdmEvDteIdleTimouts
mdmEvDteIdleTimouts.description: The number of times that the modem has had no DTE activity for the time specified by mdmEtDteIdleThresh.

mdmEvInConnectEstabs.name: mdmEvInConnectEstabs
mdmEvInConnectEstabs.description: The number of times that the modem has reported a incomming connection established event.

mdmEvOutConnectEstabs.name: mdmEvOutConnectEstabs
mdmEvOutConnectEstabs.description: The number of times that the modem has reported an outgoing connection established event.

mdmEvInConnectTerms.name: mdmEvInConnectTerms
mdmEvInConnectTerms.description: The number of times the modem has reported an incomming connection terminated event.

mdmEvOutConnectTerms.name: mdmEvOutConnectTerms
mdmEvOutConnectTerms.description: The number of times the modem has reported an outgoing connection termination event.

mdmEvConnectAttemptFails.name: mdmEvConnectAttemptFails
mdmEvConnectAttemptFails.description: The number of times the modem has reported a connect attempt failure event. This does not include those connect attempt failures that are reported due to no dial tone and no loop current.

mdmEvConnectTimouts.name: mdmEvConnectTimouts
mdmEvConnectTimouts.description: The number of times that the NMC has detected a call that has has a duration in excess of the threshold defined in mdmEtConnectThresh.

mdmEvMgmtBusFailures.name: mdmEvMgmtBusFailures
mdmEvMgmtBusFailures.description: The number of times the NMC has been unable to get a response from the modem to requests on the management bus.

mdmEvResetByDtes.name: mdmEvResetByDtes
mdmEvResetByDtes.description: The number of times that the modem has been reset by the DTE via the ATZ command or by DTR drop.

mdmEvDtrFalses.name: mdmEvDtrFalses
mdmEvDtrFalses.description: The number of times the modem has reported DTR False events. The DTR false event timeout is based on mdmEtDtrFalseThresh.

mdmEvDtrTrues.name: mdmEvDtrTrues
mdmEvDtrTrues.description: The number of times the modem has reported DTR True events. The modem reports these events to the NMC based on the value of mdmEtDtrTrueTresh.

mdmEvNoTones.name: mdmEvNoTones
mdmEvNoTones.description: The number of times the modem reported no tones.

mdmEvNoLoops.name: mdmEvNoLoops
mdmEvNoLoops.description: The number of times the modem reported no loop current events.

mdmEvBlers.name: mdmEvBlers
mdmEvBlers.description: The number of times the modem reported BLERs.

mdmEvFallBacks.name: mdmEvFallBacks
mdmEvFallBacks.description: The number of times the modem reported fall backs.

mdmEvInConnectTime.name: mdmEvInConnectTime
mdmEvInConnectTime.description: Cumulative counter for inbound call connect time.

mdmEvInTotalBytesRx.name: mdmEvInTotalBytesRx
mdmEvInTotalBytesRx.description: Cumulative counter for number of bytes received on inbound calls.

mdmEvInTotalBytesTx.name: mdmEvInTotalBytesTx
mdmEvInTotalBytesTx.description: Cumulative counter for number of bytes transmitted on inbound calls.

mdmEvOutConnectTime.name: mdmEvOutConnectTime
mdmEvOutConnectTime.description: Cumulative counter for outbound call connect time.

mdmEvOutTotalBytesRx.name: mdmEvOutTotalBytesRx
mdmEvOutTotalBytesRx.description: Cumulative counter for number of bytes received on outbound calls.

mdmEvOutTotalBytesTx.name: mdmEvOutTotalBytesTx
mdmEvOutTotalBytesTx.description: Cumulative counter for number of bytes transmitted on outbound calls.

mdmEvInConnAttemptFails.name: mdmEvInConnAttemptFails
mdmEvInConnAttemptFails.description: The number of times the modem has reported a inbound connect attempt failure event. This does not include those connect attempt failues that are reported due to no dial time and no loop current.

mdmEvOutConnAttemptFails.name: mdmEvOutConnAttemptFails
mdmEvOutConnAttemptFails.description: The number of times the modem has reported a outbound connect attempt failure event. This does not include those connect attempt failures that are reported due to no dial tone and no loop current.

mdmEtTable.name: mdmEtTable
mdmEtTable.description: Table of event thresholds used for setting up the modem to report events that can in turn be monitored by RMON.

mdmEtEntry.name: mdmEtEntry
mdmEtEntry.description: Event Thresholds that are used by the modem and the NMC to qualify certain events.

mdmEtIndex.name: mdmEtIndex
mdmEtIndex.description: Index into table used to identify the the specific modem, contians the unique value from the chassis mib entity table.

mdmEtDteIdleThresh.name: mdmEtDteIdleThresh
mdmEtDteIdleThresh.description: Defines the length of time for the modem to wait before reporting a 'DTE transmit data idle' event. (There must be no activity on the DTE transmit line for the specified quantity of minutes.

mdmEtDtrFalseThresh.name: mdmEtDtrFalseThresh
mdmEtDtrFalseThresh.description: Defines the quantity of seconds that will be used by the modem to qualify a 'DTR False' event.

mdmEtDtrTrueThresh.name: mdmEtDtrTrueThresh
mdmEtDtrTrueThresh.description: Defines the quantity of seconds that the modem will use to qualify a 'DTR True' event.

mdmEtConnTimeLimit.name: mdmEtConnTimeLimit
mdmEtConnTimeLimit.description: Defines the number of minutes that a call may be connected before triggering the 'connect timer limit' event. A value of zero for this limit means that no event is to be detected (ie. no time limit).

mdmEtBlerThresh.name: mdmEtBlerThresh
mdmEtBlerThresh.description: Defines the number of BLERs that will be used to qualify the 'BLER count at threshold' event for a given call.

mdmEtFallbackThresh.name: mdmEtFallbackThresh
mdmEtFallbackThresh.description: Defines the number of fallbacks at which the 'fallback count at threshold' event will be generated for a given call.

mdmCdTable.name: mdmCdTable
mdmCdTable.description: The command table contains an entry for each modem installed in a chassis. It provides a means for processing actions requested by the management console. The mechanism used is to set the command and get the result which will indicate the success of the request.

mdmCdEntry.name: mdmCdEntry
mdmCdEntry.description: Objects that are used to request that certain actions be taken by the modem itself or that the NMC take certain actions for the modem.

mdmCdIndex.name: mdmCdIndex
mdmCdIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the modem to which this entry is applicable. The value corresponds to the index of the corresponding modem in the entity table of the chassis MIB.

mdmCdMgtStationId.name: mdmCdMgtStationId
mdmCdMgtStationId.description: This object is a generic read-write variable that a Management Station (MS) can use to guarantee that the results from a given command are the results of a command issued by that specific MS. Each MS must SET a unique value to this object when doing commands and GET the value of this object together with uchasCmdReqId and uchasCmdResult to detect interference from other MSs.

mdmCdReqId.name: mdmCdReqId
mdmCdReqId.description: This object contains the value of the request-id field in the SNMP PDU which invoked the most recent command or test on this modem. If the request-id is unknown or undefined, this object contains the value zero.

mdmCdFunction.name: mdmCdFunction
mdmCdFunction.description: This object contains a value that describes the command that is being invoked.

mdmCdForce.name: mdmCdForce
mdmCdForce.description: In certain cases the modem may be in a state where certain commands could adversely affect connectiuons. In such cases, a command request with this object not present or set to noForce will result in a warning. If the operator elects to ignore such warnings, this object can be set to force in a subsequent request to cause the command to be carried out regardless of the potetialy hazzerdous effect.

mdmCdParam.name: mdmCdParam
mdmCdParam.description: This object can contain parameters that are specific to the particualar command being issued.

mdmCdResult.name: mdmCdResult
mdmCdResult.description: This object contains the result of the most recently requested command or test, or the value none(1) if no commands have been requested since last reset.

mdmCdCode.name: mdmCdCode
mdmCdCode.description: The value of this object indicates a further description of what went wrong when a command fails.

mdmTeTable.name: mdmTeTable
mdmTeTable.description: A table containing an enable for each trap that a modem entity is capable of generating. Some of these events occur often and traps may flood the network if care is not taken to avoid such conditions. These traps should be enabled sparingly. (usually only when debugging a problem on a particular modem)

mdmTeEntry.name: mdmTeEntry
mdmTeEntry.description: There is one modem trap enable row for each modem entity in the NAS chassis.

mdmTeIndex.name: mdmTeIndex
mdmTeIndex.description: A unique index which identifies the modem for which these trap enables pertain. The index to the trap enable table matches the index of the corresponding modem in the entity table in the chassis MIB.

mdmTeInConnEstablished.name: mdmTeInConnEstablished
mdmTeInConnEstablished.description: Enables generation of an SNMP trap upon detection of an incoming connection establishment on the specified modem.

mdmTeOutConnEstablished.name: mdmTeOutConnEstablished
mdmTeOutConnEstablished.description: Enables generation of an SNMP trap upon detection of an outgoing connection establishment on the specified modem.

mdmTeInConnTerminated.name: mdmTeInConnTerminated
mdmTeInConnTerminated.description: Enables generation of an SNMP trap upon detection of an incoming connection termination on the specified modem.

mdmTeOutConnTerminated.name: mdmTeOutConnTerminated
mdmTeOutConnTerminated.description: Enables generation of an SNMP trap upon detection of an outgoing connection terminated on the specified modem.

mdmTeConnAttemptFailure.name: mdmTeConnAttemptFailure
mdmTeConnAttemptFailure.description: Enables generation of an SNMP trap upon detection of a connection attemp failure on the specified modem.

mdmTeConnLimitExpired.name: mdmTeConnLimitExpired
mdmTeConnLimitExpired.description: Enables generation of an SNMP trap upon detection of the expiration of the connection time limit on the specified modem.

mdmTeDteXmitDataIdle.name: mdmTeDteXmitDataIdle
mdmTeDteXmitDataIdle.description: Enables generation of an SNMP trap upon detection of DTE transmit data idle on the specified modem.

mdmTeDtrTrue.name: mdmTeDtrTrue
mdmTeDtrTrue.description: Enables generation of an SNMP trap upon detection of DTR going true on the specified modem.

mdmTeDtrFalse.name: mdmTeDtrFalse
mdmTeDtrFalse.description: Enables generation of an SNMP trap upon detection of DTR going false on the specified modem.

mdmTeBlerCountAtThresh.name: mdmTeBlerCountAtThresh
mdmTeBlerCountAtThresh.description: Enables generation of an SNMP trap upon detection of the BLER count at the specified threshold on the specified modem.

mdmTeFallbkCountAtThresh.name: mdmTeFallbkCountAtThresh
mdmTeFallbkCountAtThresh.description: Enables generation of an SNMP trap upon detection of the fallback count at the specified threshold on the specified modem.

mdmTeNoDialTone.name: mdmTeNoDialTone
mdmTeNoDialTone.description: Enables generation of an SNMP trap upon detection of no dial tone on the specified modem.

mdmTeNoLoopCurrent.name: mdmTeNoLoopCurrent
mdmTeNoLoopCurrent.description: Enables generation of an SNMP trap upon detection of no loop current on the specified modem.

mdmTeResetByDTE.name: mdmTeResetByDTE
mdmTeResetByDTE.description: Enables generation of an SNMP trap upon detection of reset by DTE on the specified modem.

mdmTeDialOutCallDur.name: mdmTeDialOutCallDur
mdmTeDialOutCallDur.description: Enables the dial out (from the NMC) call duration trap. Default = disable(2).

mdmTeDialInCallDur.name: mdmTeDialInCallDur
mdmTeDialInCallDur.description: Enables the dial in (to the NMC) call duration trap. Default = disable(2).

mdmTePbActive.name: mdmTePbActive
mdmTePbActive.description: Enables the Packet Bus Active. Default = disable(2).

mdmTePbLost.name: mdmTePbLost
mdmTePbLost.description: Enables the Packet Bus Lost trap. Default = disable(2).

mdmTeDteRingNoAns.name: mdmTeDteRingNoAns
mdmTeDteRingNoAns.description: Enables the Dte Ring No Answer trap. Default = disable(2).

mdmTePbClockLossEvent.name: mdmTePbClockLossEvent
mdmTePbClockLossEvent.description: This object is used to disable the ability for a NAC to report when the packet bus clock has been lost. Default = disableAll(2).

mdmTePbClockRestoreEvent.name: mdmTePbClockRestoreEvent
mdmTePbClockRestoreEvent.description: This object is used to disable the ability for a NAC to report when the packet bus clock has been restored. Default = disableAll(2).

mdmTeInConnAttemptFail.name: mdmTeInConnAttemptFail
mdmTeInConnAttemptFail.description: Enables generation of a SNMP trap upon detection of an inbound connection attempt failure on the specified modem.

mdmTeOutConnAttemptFail.name: mdmTeOutConnAttemptFail
mdmTeOutConnAttemptFail.description: Enables generation of a SNMP trap upon detection of an outbound connection attempt failure on the specified modem.

mdmTe105ResponderTest.name: mdmTe105ResponderTest
mdmTe105ResponderTest.description: Enables generation of a SNMP trap upon detection of a 105 responder test on the specified modem.

mdmLsTable.name: mdmLsTable
mdmLsTable.description: A table defining all the Link Security parameters for each modem in the chassis.

mdmLsTableEntry.name: mdmLsTableEntry
mdmLsTableEntry.description: Link Security parameters for a modem. These define the link level security operations which take place when a call is negotiated.

mdmLsIndex.name: mdmLsIndex
mdmLsIndex.description: The index which uniquely identifies the modem to which this entry is applicable. The value corresponds to the value of the index to the entity table in the chassis MIB that corresponds to the same modem.

mdmLsSecurityEnable.name: mdmLsSecurityEnable
mdmLsSecurityEnable.description: Allows to disable/enable the dial security feature for the modem.

mdmLsFallbackPromptEnable.name: mdmLsFallbackPromptEnable
mdmLsFallbackPromptEnable.description: Disables/enables the prompting by the called modem when the auto pass password supplied by the caller fails or if no password is supplied at all.

mdmLsForcePromptEnable.name: mdmLsForcePromptEnable
mdmLsForcePromptEnable.description: If this is enabled, the modem will prompt the remote user for a password regardless of the success of the modem to negotiate the auto pass password.

mdmLsLocAccPasswdEnable.name: mdmLsLocAccPasswdEnable
mdmLsLocAccPasswdEnable.description: Disables/enables the Local Access Password feature used to establish security check when accessing any security setting.

mdmLsDialBackEnable.name: mdmLsDialBackEnable
mdmLsDialBackEnable.description: If this is set to enable the modem, after successful password validation, will disconnect and dial out to the originating modem.

mdmLsAutoPassPasswd.name: mdmLsAutoPassPasswd
mdmLsAutoPassPasswd.description: Contains the Auto Pass Password used for establishing Link security during call negotiation.

mdmLsLocalAccessPasswd.name: mdmLsLocalAccessPasswd
mdmLsLocalAccessPasswd.description: Contains the Local Access password used when accessing any security setting and when Local Access password feature is enabled.

mdmLsAccountPasswd.name: mdmLsAccountPasswd
mdmLsAccountPasswd.description: Contains the fall back password which must be entered if auto pass password is not satisfied.

mdmHsTable.name: mdmHsTable
mdmHsTable.description: A table containing the Hub security parameters accessible in the modem.

mdmHsEntry.name: mdmHsEntry
mdmHsEntry.description: There is one entry in this table for each modem entity found in the chassis mib entity table.

mdmHsIndex.name: mdmHsIndex
mdmHsIndex.description: An index that uniquely identifies the modem to which this row in the Hub Security table pertains. The value of this index matches the value of the index for the corresonding entity in the entity table of the Chassis MIB.

mdmHsDialInEnable.name: mdmHsDialInEnable
mdmHsDialInEnable.description: Allows the modem to be configured for dial-in security. Enabling this effectively disables the modem's built-in Link security operation. The default for this object is disabled.

mdmHsDialOutEnable.name: mdmHsDialOutEnable
mdmHsDialOutEnable.description: Allows modems to be configured for dial-out security. Enabling this effectively disables the modem's built-in link security operation. The default value for this object is disabled.

mdmHsDtrDcdDelay.name: mdmHsDtrDcdDelay
mdmHsDtrDcdDelay.description: Allows configuration of the time delay (in 100ths of a second) between reciept of DTR and assertion of DCD when the user on an incomming security call has successfully compleated the security dialog. This object only applies to modems using an RS232 like interface.

mdmHsDtrDsrDelay.name: mdmHsDtrDsrDelay
mdmHsDtrDsrDelay.description: Allows configuration of the delay (in 100ths of a second) between detection of DTR and assertion of DSR when an incomming security call has completed security negotiation successfully.

mdmArTable.name: mdmArTable
mdmArTable.description: Table of auto response scripts for each modem in the chassis. The number of table entries is specified by modemNumber.

mdmArEntry.name: mdmArEntry
mdmArEntry.description: List of configurable auto response scripts.

mdmArIndex.name: mdmArIndex
mdmArIndex.description: Index in to the auto response table. This index contains the unique value associated with the modem as defined in the chassis mib entity table.

mdmArIncomConnectEstab.name: mdmArIncomConnectEstab
mdmArIncomConnectEstab.description: This script is triggered when a Total Control WAN HUB modem establishes a connection with a remote modem. The remote modem is the caller.

mdmArOutgoConnectEstab.name: mdmArOutgoConnectEstab
mdmArOutgoConnectEstab.description: This script is triggered when a Total Control WAN HUB modem establishes a connection with a remote modem. The Total Control WAN HUB modem is the caller.

mdmArIncomConnectTerm.name: mdmArIncomConnectTerm
mdmArIncomConnectTerm.description: This script is triggered after a remote modem has called a Total Control WAN HUB modem, but the connection between them terminated for some reason.

mdmArOutgoConnectTerm.name: mdmArOutgoConnectTerm
mdmArOutgoConnectTerm.description: This script is triggered after a Total Control WAN HUB modem called a remote modem, but the connection between them terminated for some reason.

mdmArConnectAttemptFail.name: mdmArConnectAttemptFail
mdmArConnectAttemptFail.description: This script is triggered when a Total Control WAN HUB modem fails to connect with a remote modem for an incoming or an outgoing call.

mdmArConnectTimeExpire.name: mdmArConnectTimeExpire
mdmArConnectTimeExpire.description: This script is triggered when a connection duration exceeds the user defined connection time limit.

mdmArResetByDte.name: mdmArResetByDte
mdmArResetByDte.description: This script is triggered when a modem has been reset by a DTE.

mdmArDteXmitIdle.name: mdmArDteXmitIdle
mdmArDteXmitIdle.description: This script is triggered when a modem's DTE remains idle for specified amount of minutes that is defined by a user.

mdmArBlersAtThresh.name: mdmArBlersAtThresh
mdmArBlersAtThresh.description: This script is triggered when a Total Control WAN HUB modem receives a certain amount of block errors. This amount can be configured by a user.

mdmArFbacksAtThresh.name: mdmArFbacksAtThresh
mdmArFbacksAtThresh.description: This script is triggered when a Total Control WAN HUB modem reaches a certain amount of fall backs within a single session. This amount can be configured by a user.

mdmArDialOutLoginFail.name: mdmArDialOutLoginFail
mdmArDialOutLoginFail.description: This script is triggered when a user, who is attempting to dial out from a Total Control WAN HUB modem that supports dial security, enters an invalid response to a prompt.

mdmArDialOutRestrNum.name: mdmArDialOutRestrNum
mdmArDialOutRestrNum.description: This script is triggered when a user, who is attempting to dial out from a Total Control WAN HUB modem that supports dial security, uses a restricted number.

mdmArDialInLoginFail.name: mdmArDialInLoginFail
mdmArDialInLoginFail.description: This script is triggered when a user, who is attempting to dial in from a remote modem in to a Total Control WAN HUB modem that supports dial security, enters an invalid response to a prompt.

mdmArDialBackRestrNum.name: mdmArDialBackRestrNum
mdmArDialBackRestrNum.description: This script is triggered when a user, who is attempting to dial in from a remote modem in to a Total Control WAN HUB modem that supports dial security, requests the Total Control WAN HUB modem to dial back to a restricted number.

mdmArDialBackRestModem.name: mdmArDialBackRestModem
mdmArDialBackRestModem.description: This script is triggered when a user, who is attempting to dial in from a remote modem in to a Total Control WAN HUB modem that supports dial security, requests the Total Control WAN HUB modem to dial back using a restricted Total Control WAN HUB modem.

mdmArLoginAttemptsExceed.name: mdmArLoginAttemptsExceed
mdmArLoginAttemptsExceed.description: This script is triggered when a user, who is dialing in to or out of the Total Control WAN HUB modem, exceeds the number of correct user name/password response attempts.

mdmArUserBlacklisted.name: mdmArUserBlacklisted
mdmArUserBlacklisted.description: This script is triggered when a user, who is dialing in to or out of the Total Control WAN HUB modem, exceeds the number of password prompt retries. At this point the user becomes black listed.

mdmArAttmpLoginByBlistUsr.name: mdmArAttmpLoginByBlistUsr
mdmArAttmpLoginByBlistUsr.description: This script is triggered when a user, who has been black listed, is trying to dial in to or out of a Total Control WAN HUB modem.

mdmArRspAttemptLimExceed.name: mdmArRspAttemptLimExceed
mdmArRspAttemptLimExceed.description: This script is triggered when a user, who is dialing in to or out of a Total Control WAN HUB modem, exceeds the number of security prompt retries during a single dial security session.

mdmArWatchdog.name: mdmArWatchdog
mdmArWatchdog.description: This script is triggered when a software failure has occurred on a modem.

mdmArMgtBusFailure.name: mdmArMgtBusFailure
mdmArMgtBusFailure.description: This script is triggered when a contact with a modem, via the management bus, has been lost.

mdmArDtrTrue.name: mdmArDtrTrue
mdmArDtrTrue.description: This script is triggered when a modem's DTE transitions it DTR line from low to high and holds it high for the specified number of seconds. This amount is user configurable.

mdmArDtrFalse.name: mdmArDtrFalse
mdmArDtrFalse.description: This script is triggered when a modem's DTE transitions it DTR line from high to low and holds it low for the specified number of seconds. This amount is user configurable.

mdmArMdmRingNoAnswer.name: mdmArMdmRingNoAnswer
mdmArMdmRingNoAnswer.description: This script is triggered when a Total Control WAN HUB modem, configured for auto answer, fails to answer an incoming call within a specified number of rings. This amount is user configurable.

mdmArDteRingNoAnswer.name: mdmArDteRingNoAnswer
mdmArDteRingNoAnswer.description: This script is triggered when a DTE fials to raise DTR in response to an incoming call for a specified amount of rings. This amount is user configurable.

mdmArNoDialTone.name: mdmArNoDialTone
mdmArNoDialTone.description: This script is triggered when a Total Control WAN HUB modem goes off hook, but detects an inadequate dial tone level on an analog phone line.

mdmArNoLoopCurrent.name: mdmArNoLoopCurrent
mdmArNoLoopCurrent.description: This script is triggered when a Total Control WAN HUB modem goes off hook, but it does not detect the presence of loop current on an analog phone line.

mdmArTimer1.name: mdmArTimer1
mdmArTimer1.description: This script is triggered when the first general purpose timer expires.

mdmArTimer2.name: mdmArTimer2
mdmArTimer2.description: This script is triggered when the second general purpose timer expires.

mdmArTimer3.name: mdmArTimer3
mdmArTimer3.description: This script is triggered when the third general purpose timer expires.

mdmArTimer4.name: mdmArTimer4
mdmArTimer4.description: This script is triggered when the fourth general purpose timer expires.

mdmArPacketBusActive.name: mdmArPacketBusActive
mdmArPacketBusActive.description: This script is triggered when a packet bus active event is detected by the modem.

mdmArPacketBusLost.name: mdmArPacketBusLost
mdmArPacketBusLost.description: This script is triggered when a packet bus lost event is detected by the modem.

mdmCeTable.name: mdmCeTable
mdmCeTable.description: A list of configurable Cellular Support object for a modem. The number of table entries is given by modemNumber.

mdmCeEntry.name: mdmCeEntry
mdmCeEntry.description: Objects which define the Cellular characteristics for a particular modem.

mdmCeIndex.name: mdmCeIndex
mdmCeIndex.description: This index value which uniquely identifies the modem to which this entry is applicable. The value corresponds to the index of the corresponding modem in the entity table of the chassis MIB.

mdmCeMnp10Dis.name: mdmCeMnp10Dis
mdmCeMnp10Dis.description: This object is bit 0 of S-register 60. It disable/enables MNP10 negotiation mostly used with cellular operations. (defualt=0)

mdmCeMnpxDis.name: mdmCeMnpxDis
mdmCeMnpxDis.description: This object is bit 1 of S-register 60. It will enable/disable the MNP extended services to be active during negotiation. This will mean that MNP10 will use V.42 to negotiate. (defualt=0)

mdmCeComp.name: mdmCeComp
mdmCeComp.description: This object is bit 2 of S-register 60. It selects which compression type will be negotiated if allowed by other modem settings. (default =0>

mdmCeOperDis.name: mdmCeOperDis
mdmCeOperDis.description: This object is bit 3 of S-register 60. It announces that at least one end of the link will be across a cellular network. Therefore, the Dyncamic Transmit Algorithm will be active. (default=0)

mdmCeLinkSpeed.name: mdmCeLinkSpeed
mdmCeLinkSpeed.description: This object is bit 4 of register 60 tells the modem which speed to establish the link at. (default=0)

mdmCeShortFormRules.name: mdmCeShortFormRules
mdmCeShortFormRules.description: This object is the S-register 61. It takes a value from 0 to 3 and regulates the V.42bis Short Form Negotiation rules. The short form assumes that the maximum string length is always 32 octets and that the direction of compression is always bi-directional. (default=0)

mdmCeDceBitraLim.name: mdmCeDceBitraLim
mdmCeDceBitraLim.description: This object is the S-register 64. It limits DCE bitrates to values equal to or below the chosen setting. (default=0)

mdmCeDceTxLev.name: mdmCeDceTxLev
mdmCeDceTxLev.description: This object is S-register 65. It selects DCE TX level to use during cellular operations. (default=0)

mdmCeV42EtcDis.name: mdmCeV42EtcDis
mdmCeV42EtcDis.description: This object is the bit 0 of S-register 66. It enables/disables ETC. (default=0)

mdmCeV42CellSite.name: mdmCeV42CellSite
mdmCeV42CellSite.description: This object is the bit 1 of S-register 66. It selects fixed or mobile site operations. (default=0)

mdmCeV42EtcCallToneDis.name: mdmCeV42EtcCallToneDis
mdmCeV42EtcCallToneDis.description: This object is the bit 2 of S-register 66. It enables/disables ETC calling tone. (default=0)

mdmCeV42EtcTxLevConDis.name: mdmCeV42EtcTxLevConDis
